body:
`continue` within a `switch` statement would continue checking cases below for their validity.

This would be in contrast to `fallthrough` which just executes all the other branches below, this only executes VALID branches below.

an example of a fizzbuzz using the continue within switch:
```go
package main

func main(){
	for i := 1; i<101; i++ {
		fizzbuzz(i)
	}
}

func fizzbuzz(num int) {
	// when num=15 all branches would be hit.
	fizzSwitch: switch {
	case true:
		print(num)
		continue fizzSwitch // continues to check other cases for true also
	case num%3==0:
		print("fizz")
		continue fizzSwitch // continues to check other cases for true also
	case num%5==0:
		print("buzz")
		continue fizzSwitch // continues to check other cases for true also
	case true:
		print(num)
	}
}
```
